he book's varied and carefully selected contributions, written by experts from around 20 countries, seek to answer such questions as: ·  how have modernism and the avant-garde responded to historical circumstance in mapping the form of possible futures for humanity?·  how have avant-garde and modernist works presented ideals of living as alternatives to the present?·  how have avant-gardists acted with or against the state to remodel human life or to resist the instrumental reduction of life by administration and industrialisation?   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aAesthetics, ModernxThemes, motives. 0aArts, EuropeanxThemes, motives. 0aAvant-garde (Aesthetics) 0aUtopias in art. 4aUtopia. 4aavant-garde. 4amodernism. 70(DE-601)1046587110(DE-588)4039827-4aModerne2gnd 70(DE-601)1048058110(DE-588)4133965-4aAvantgarde2gnd 70(DE-601)1062199600(DE-588)4041251-9aUtopie2gnd 70(DE-601)1062573150(DE-588)4033422-3aKünste2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAyers, David, eeditor.1 aHjartarson, Benedikt, eeditor.1 aHuttunen, Tomi, eeditor.1 aVeivo, Harri, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2015z9783110438673oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831104330050 cprintz978311042709740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110434781423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110434781.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-D